794
00:50:56,770 --> 00:51:01,410
Thanks to the children, I'm living my life properly.

795
00:51:01,410 --> 00:51:03,940
So I should be thanking them!

796
00:51:03,940 --> 00:51:07,370
What did they do so wrong?

797
00:51:08,210 --> 00:51:10,780
One gets pushed around by his mom,

798
00:51:10,780 --> 00:51:14,140
and the other gets shoved around by his aunt.

799
00:51:14,140 --> 00:51:16,160
Hae Joon, that child?

800
00:51:16,160 --> 00:51:21,480
He does his absolute best to help me with whatever I'm doing.

801
00:51:21,480 --> 00:51:25,300
He does all he has to, including basketball, cleaning, and laundry.

802
00:51:25,300 --> 00:51:28,100
He's such a nice boy.

803
00:51:28,100 --> 00:51:32,560
Wh-What on earth did he do so wrong that

804
00:51:32,560 --> 00:51:35,410
he has to be good to me?

805
00:51:35,410 --> 00:51:37,540
Be good...

806
00:51:37,540 --> 00:51:41,850
J-Just how much more does he have to do?

807
00:51:44,310 --> 00:51:47,090
Th-That's not what I meant...

808
00:51:47,980 --> 00:51:49,590
He knows.

809
00:51:50,210 --> 00:51:52,890
He knows that's not what you meant.

810
00:51:53,940 --> 00:51:55,930
He's just drunk, you know.

811
00:51:55,930 --> 00:51:57,350
You understand, right?

812
00:51:57,350 --> 00:51:59,410
I'm sorry.

813
00:51:59,410 --> 00:52:01,810
I'm so sorry.

814
00:52:26,050 --> 00:52:28,280
Aigoo, seriously.

815
00:52:34,020 --> 00:52:36,230
He went all out today.

816
00:52:36,230 --> 00:52:39,950
What a memorable birthday today will be.

817
00:52:42,260 --> 00:52:45,180
- His socks. 
 - Yes.

818
00:52:53,810 --> 00:52:55,780
This is a clean one.

819
00:52:58,300 --> 00:53:01,300
- I'm a fool, aren't I? 
 - Not at all.

820
00:53:02,300 --> 00:53:04,270
Just leave it.

821
00:53:05,110 --> 00:53:08,490
I'll clean up with Hae Joon once he comes out.

822
00:53:08,490 --> 00:53:10,960
I can just clean up quickly.

823
00:53:10,960 --> 00:53:13,560
You and Hae Joon aren't the same.

824
00:53:13,560 --> 00:53:19,090
Even if you ate and grew up together, your dad pays for everything.

825
00:53:19,090 --> 00:53:23,200
I'll clean up before leaving. Go up and get some rest.

826
00:53:23,200 --> 00:53:25,510
We are the same.

827
00:53:25,510 --> 00:53:26,780
What?

828
00:53:26,780 --> 00:53:29,240
Hae Joon and I are the same.

829
00:53:29,860 --> 00:53:32,930
My dad doesn't just pay for everything.

830
00:53:32,930 --> 00:53:37,080
And Ahjusshi doesn't think of Hae Joon and me that way, either.

831
00:53:38,390 --> 00:53:40,710
You don't need to worry.

832
00:53:46,330 --> 00:53:47,730
Come and take the plates.

833
00:53:47,730 --> 00:53:49,030
Okay.

834
00:53:49,030 --> 00:53:51,990
You should see your aunt off.

835
00:53:51,990 --> 00:53:53,570
Yes.

836
00:53:54,720 --> 00:53:56,400
Let's go.

837
00:54:00,200 --> 00:54:02,970
We should've just called a taxi to Ohryun Mansion.

838
00:54:02,970 --> 00:54:05,110
It's fine.

839
00:54:05,110 --> 00:54:09,470
I think it would feel suffocating if I got in a car right now.

840
00:54:10,710 --> 00:54:13,440
I haven't cried in a long time.

841
00:54:13,440 --> 00:54:17,730
Crying feels a bit refreshing, too.

842
00:54:18,630 --> 00:54:20,350
Is that so?

843
00:54:26,790 --> 00:54:28,890
I'm sorry, Hae Joon.

844
00:54:28,890 --> 00:54:31,460
What is it this time?

845
00:54:32,660 --> 00:54:35,800
I don't know. I don't know,

846
00:54:35,800 --> 00:54:38,350
but I know I'm at fault.

847
00:54:38,350 --> 00:54:39,920
You didn't do anything wrong, Auntie.

848
00:54:39,920 --> 00:54:42,200
Dad was just a bit upset today.

849
00:54:42,200 --> 00:54:44,830
I understand how you feel.

850
00:54:49,560 --> 00:54:51,030
Hae Joon.

851
00:54:51,030 --> 00:54:52,500
Yes.

852
00:54:53,660 --> 00:54:55,980
You should forget your mom, too.

853
00:54:56,980 --> 00:55:01,420
Just think she was never there to begin with.

854
00:55:03,250 --> 00:55:06,200
You just need to be good to Joo Won's dad.

855
00:55:08,450 --> 00:55:10,330
Just forget...

856
00:55:11,600 --> 00:55:13,570
about your mom.

857
00:55:20,100 --> 00:55:23,720
I mean, should I not say this, either?

858
00:55:25,130 --> 00:55:27,190
I don't think about Mom.

859
00:55:27,190 --> 00:55:29,690
I can't even remember her face now.

860
00:55:33,850 --> 00:55:35,440
I see.

861
00:55:38,000 --> 00:55:42,960
I'll be good to Dad and to you, too, Auntie.

862
00:55:42,960 --> 00:55:45,650
I'm going to repay everyone.

863
00:55:45,650 --> 00:55:49,630
You don't need to worry about a thing.

864
00:55:49,630 --> 00:55:51,070
Auntie.

865
00:55:53,410 --> 00:55:55,130
You trust me, right?

866
00:55:59,360 --> 00:56:01,650
Come on. Don't cry, okay?

867
00:56:03,310 --> 00:56:05,310
I'll be good.

868
00:56:29,750 --> 00:56:32,000
What time is it?

869
00:56:34,400 --> 00:56:37,300
It's not midnight yet.

870
00:56:44,710 --> 00:56:46,620
What about Auntie?

871
00:56:47,770 --> 00:56:49,610
She got home safe.

872
00:56:49,610 --> 00:56:52,710
She said to tell you she was sorry.

873
00:56:52,710 --> 00:56:56,040
I brought you water and medicine for a hangover.

874
00:56:56,040 --> 00:56:58,270
Auntie bought them for you.

875
00:56:58,270 --> 00:57:01,700
Make sure to brush your teeth.

876
00:57:01,700 --> 00:57:05,080
Underwear for tomorrow... in the drawer...

877
00:57:05,080 --> 00:57:07,280
I know.

878
00:57:08,530 --> 00:57:11,070
Have a good night, Father.

879
00:57:12,280 --> 00:57:13,950
There.

880
00:57:32,470 --> 00:57:34,820
What about Auntie? Is she okay?

881
00:57:34,820 --> 00:57:36,780
Yes. Well...

882
00:57:37,780 --> 00:57:42,610
I guess Auntie was relieved to hear what you said.

883
00:57:47,290 --> 00:57:49,650
Cut it out.

884
00:57:49,650 --> 00:57:51,960
Yes, stop it.

885
00:57:53,370 --> 00:57:55,550
19-year-old Kang Hae Joon

886
00:57:55,550 --> 00:58:00,160
starts to feel lonely in the corner of his heart after his aunt leaves.

887
00:58:00,160 --> 00:58:02,490
Come on.

888
00:58:02,490 --> 00:58:04,860
All yours.

